# AC-FDL-4 (conversion variant): .!code probe equals #TYPE_MISMATCH literal
#
# guard catches the type-assertion halt and the invalid value carries
# a #TYPE_MISMATCH status code. .!code materialises the atom as a
# :code value; comparing it to the #TYPE_MISMATCH literal returns true.
# Both runtimes produce byte-equal results via the shared @rcrsr/rill runtime.

guard { "hello" -> :number } => $x
$x.!code == #TYPE_MISMATCH
